Root cause looks straightforward: critical query paths on `orders` are almost certainly scanning 500M rows because there’s no secondary index at all—just the PK on `id`. The highest-probability missing index is `user_id`, which is the classic hot lookup for order history/account pages and many operational queries. I’m creating that index with `CONCURRENTLY` to avoid blocking writes, then I’ll verify it and recheck locks.
